Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes

Review: This film is available for free on Vimeo! Enjoy :) vimeo.com/417062331

The story was charming and sweet, tho I did feel torn between the first and seconf half of the film. The first half was unsatisfying in terms of technical aspects like the animation being too blend (the environments needed another pass and more detail, particularly in the sequence where they reveal Nimona's shapeshifting) and the comedy coming from cliché or cheap jokes. The second half, however, was a lot more nuanced--that's the story they wanted to tell.

Almodovar here excels at making a film with great performances, striking use of color, unapologetically corny dialogue and thoughtful editing. The overall arc of tension built and climaxed excellently. But please, more footage of gay Pascal. I really wanted this to be longer and not to cut the sex scene out. Otherwise a wonderful campy film.
Thanks whomever added this to the database! You can check out this film on YouTube :) youtu.be/5LHLjsapkmY

This epic action-drama Tollywood bromance flick tells the story of two revolutionaries against the British Raj in the 1920's. It has probably the best action sequences and use of cinematography I've seen in Indian cinema, with Bollywood-influenced use of melodrama and musical sequences, echoes of revolutionary movies like Lagaan mixed with Ramayama references, and a bromance that directly resembles that of the classic 1975 film Sholay.
